headline.main: Jim Rathmann, 83, Dies; Winner of 1960 Indy 500

results.snippet: In his 1979 book about America's first generation of astronauts, Tom Wolfe spoke of the quality they most prized, ''an uncritical willingness to face danger.'' They called it the right stuff, a phrase that became the book's title.     The...
results.lead_paragraph: In his 1979 book about America's first generation of astronauts, Tom Wolfe spoke of the quality they most prized, ''an uncritical willingness to face danger.'' They called it the right stuff, a phrase that became the book's title. The highest-flying heroes of the 1960s saw the right stuff in a seemingly unlikely man, Jim Rathmann, who owned a Chevy dealership near Cape Canaveral and who returned their admiration, leasing to them for very little money his muscular Corvettes.

results.abstract: Zdenek Miler, Czech animator who created Krtek the mole, a cartoon character that drew audiences in over 80 countries, dies at age 90. Photo (M)0

headline.main: Zdenek Miler, 90, Animator Who Created Krtek the Mole

results.snippet: Krtek, a snub-nosed, wide-eyed mole, has delighted cartoon lovers around the world for more than 50 years. Gently, cheerfully and almost always wordlessly, he has prodded bureaucrats, come to the aid of those in need and lamented the destruction of...
results.lead_paragraph: Krtek, a snub-nosed, wide-eyed mole, has delighted cartoon lovers around the world for more than 50 years. Gently, cheerfully and almost always wordlessly, he has prodded bureaucrats, come to the aid of those in need and lamented the destruction of the environment. In one adventure, he finds his forest invaded by voracious builders but manages to secure a new home in a nearby forest (with the help of a slip of paper from a high-ranking official). In another, he roams the world and is stunned by an American mole's superior burrowing technology.

results.abstract: A student from Minnesota worries that the "me of today'' isn't qualified to make decisions for the "me of the future."

headline.main: 'The Kid Who Likes English Class' Wonders What to Do About College

results.snippet: A student from Minnesota worries that the "me of today'' isn't qualified to make decisions for the "me of the future."
results.lead_paragraph: My best friend asked me last week, "Where are you even applying?" and I avoided her question.  Mostly because I just don't want to talk about college.  These applications have been hanging over my head for months and I'm still not finished, still not done mulling over them.  Even with my best friend I don't want to talk about it.  It makes me anxious to think about what I still have left to do before the Jan. 1 deadline.

results.abstract: A sun-skimming comet provides a cosmic display for NASA solar probes and astronauts.

headline.main: After Skirting the Sun, Comet Lovejoy Provides a Cosmic Show

results.snippet: A sun-skimming comet provides a cosmic display for NASA solar probes and astronauts.
results.lead_paragraph: Several days after newly discovered Comet Lovejoy streaked through the Sun's atmosphere (see video above), it provided a glorious pre-holiday display for astronauts aboard the International Space Station. NASA has posted an informative description of the comet's journey and its discovery earlier this month by Tom Lovejoy, an amateur astronomer in Australia.
